<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/91: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-03T23:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                        1921—11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 4—7
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>641. Referring your 436, August 2. Curzon says any date United States
                            desires will be agreeable to Great Britain. He understands that we will
                            suggest such date to other Governments concerned.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>